<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-097-380  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 097 380.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Feb 20 1989 n302 p80(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Blue Chip pushes new computers through specialty stores. (BlueChip International Inc.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Dunker, Mauricio.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Blue Chip International Inc Pres John Rossi says his company wantsto expand the specialty-store-channel end of the business and willuse speciality stores to sell its latest microcomputers, the BlueChip 286 AT and the Blue Chip 386.andP;  Rossi says his other productsare sold through mass merchandisers, but he expects to add 200speciality-store dealers by the end of 1989 to sell the 286 and386 microcomputers.andP;  The Blue Chip 286 AT comes in 12configurations, depending on memory requirements and sells for$1,599 to $2,799.andP;  The Blue Chip 386 has a 16MHz and a 20MHzversion, both zero-wait-state designed.andP;  The price for the 386starts at $3,199.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Blue Chip International Inc. (marketing).andO;Product:   Blue Chip 286 AT (Microcomputer)Blue Chip 386 (Microcomputer).andO;Topic:     Computer RetailingValue-Added ResellersDealers and AgentsDistributorsMarketing Strategy.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>